SIMPLE: plash
RECORDS: 5

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plash
<hw>Plash</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OD. <ets>plasch</ets>.
See <er>Plash</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small pool
of standing water; a puddle.</def> <au>Bacon.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧These shallow
<xex>plashes</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Barrow.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dash of water; a splash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Plash
<hw>Plash</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Plashed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Plashing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. D. <ets>plassen</ets>, G.
<ets>platschen</ets>. Cf. <er>Splash</er>.]</ety> <def>To dabble in
water; to splash.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Plashing</xex> among bedded
pebbles.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Keats.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Far below him <qex>plashed</qex> the waters.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Plash
<hw>Plash</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To splash, as
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To splash or sprinkle with coloring matter; <as>as,
to <ex>plash</ex> a wall in imitation of granite</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Plash
<hw>Plash</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Plashed</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Plashing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OF. <ets>plaissier</ets>,
<ets>plessier</ets>, to bend. Cf. <er>Pleach</er>.]</ety> <def>To cut
partly, or to bend and intertwine the branches of; <as>as, to
<ex>plash</ex> a hedge</as>.</def> <rj><au>Evelyn.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plash</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Plash
<hw>Plash</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The branch of a tree partly cut or
bent, and bound to, or intertwined with, other branches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plashet</ent>⟦br⟧
